	Poisoning rodents can leave carcasses hidden in places you 
wouldn't normally access.
With luck they'll get dehydrated, but I wouldn't count on it. 
Trapping is better.  Don't omit to nail down the trap, as it can be 
dragged away by the dying rodent to one of those hidden dying-spots.

